Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
hiliteFeedthroughNets(25.10)                      hiliteFeedthroughNets(25.10)

Name
       hiliteFeedthroughNets  -  Highlights  all  nets  for  which feedthrough
       buffers were inserted with the insertPtnFeedthrough command

Syntax
       hiliteFeedthroughNets

       [-help]

       <fileName>

       [<netNameList> ]

       Highlights all nets for which feedthrough buffers  were  inserted  with
       the insertPtnFeedthrough command. The highlighted feedthrough path con-
       sists  of  the  nets,  the  terms that the nets connect to, and the in-
       stances that contain those terms.

       Note: For the hiliteFeedthroughNets to work,  the  insertPtnFeedthrough
       command  must  be  run  with the -netMapping parameter. The net mapping
       file generated with the insertPtnFeedthrough -netMapping  parameter  is
       used  by the hiliteFeedthroughNets command to highlight the feedthrough
       nets.

       To dehighlight the feedthrough nets, run the dehighlight command.

       Note: It displays a warning message when used for a design with  nested
       partitions and generates results based on single level partitions.

Parameters
       <fileName>
              Specifies  the  net mapping file that was generated with the in-
              sertPtnFeedthrough -netMapping parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each hiliteFeedthroughNets parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man hiliteFeedthroughNets

       <netNameList>
              Specifies the name of the net(s) whose feedthrough  path  should
              be highlighted.

              Default:  The feedthrough paths of all nets specified in the net
              mapping file are highlighted.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              * The following command highlights all feedthrough  nets  speci-
                fied in the net mapping file nmpFile1.

                hiliteFeedthroughNets nmpFile1

              * The following command highlights all feedthrough nets that are
                specified  in  the net mapping file nmpFile1 whose name begins
                with feedthruNet_core.

                hiliteFeedthroughNets nmpFile1 feedthruNet_core*

